The paper deals with action recognition in egocentric videos using neural networks, which is a problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of multitask learning is a key aspect of the paper, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves predicting hand locations and gaze-based visual saliency, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
